{"word":"H24 - אָבִיב - ʼâbîyb - aw-beeb' - Abib","slug":"H24","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אָבִיב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼâbîyb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-beeb'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Abib"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D1;&#x05D9;&#x05D1; - 'a&#x0302;b&#x0131;&#x0302;yb</b> - <i>aw-beeb'</i><p/>From an unused root (meaning to <i>be tender</i>); <i>green</i>, that is a young <i>ear</i> of grain; hence the name of the month <i>Abib</i> or Nisan: - Abib, ear, green ears of corn."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3\">H3</a>, <a href=\"#/H5\">H5</a>"}]}